@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="privacy-policy">
    <h2>1. General Information</h2>
    <p>
        This Privacy Policy defines the rules for processing and protecting the personal data of users using the CoolFan website, which is used to manage the cooling system (fan). The data controller is [Company Name] located at [Company Address].
    </p>

    <h2>2. Scope of Data Collected</h2>
    <p>While using the CoolFan website, we may collect the following personal data:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>First and last name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Login data (username, password)</li>
        <li>IP address</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Purpose of Data Processing</h2>
    <p>User personal data is processed for the purpose of:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Ensuring the correct operation of the site and the fan management system</li>
        <li>Enabling user login and authentication</li>
        <li>Sending information about updates and changes to the system</li>
        <li>Improving the quality of services and adapting them to user needs</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Legal Basis for Data Processing</h2>
    <p>
        Personal data is processed based on the user's consent, which is expressed by voluntarily using the CoolFan service and filling out registration forms.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
        The administrator makes every effort to provide appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the processed personal data against unauthorized access, loss, modification, or deletion.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Transfer</h2>
    <p>
        User personal data may be transferred to third parties only to the extent necessary to provide the services offered by the CoolFan website, such as hosting or technical support. This data will not be transferred to third countries or international organizations.
    </p>

    <h2>7. User Rights</h2>
    <p>Users have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access their personal data</li>
        <li>Rectify, delete, or restrict the processing of their data</li>
        <li>Object to data processing</li>
        <li>Data portability</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent to data processing at any time</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        To exercise these rights, the user should contact the data administrator at the email address: [administrator's email address].
    </p>

    <h2>8. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        The CoolFan website uses cookies to ensure proper operation and improve the functionality of the service. The user can change the cookie settings in their web browser at any time.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to the Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        The administrator reserves the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy. Users will be informed of any changes via the website.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
        If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy or the processing of personal data, please contact us at the email address: [administrator's email address] or at the postal address: [company address].
    </p>

    <p><strong>Last updated: 03.VII.2024</strong></p>
</div>

<style>
    .privacy-policy {
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

        .privacy-policy h2 {
            margin-top: 20px;
            color: #2c3e50;
        }

        .privacy-policy ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        .privacy-policy p, .privacy-policy ul {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
</style>
